OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FSacked Twitter staff in    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FGhana finally get pay-off  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, X, formerly known as Twitter, has      
OL,6, finally paid off the staff it sacked in
OL,7, its African headquarters more than a   
OL,8, year after they were laid off, the     
OL,9, agency which represents them has said. 
OL,11,FMost had only been in the job, based in
OL,12,FGhana's capital, Accra, for a few      
OL,13,Fmonths when the social media platform  
OL,14,Ffired them in November 2022.           
OL,16,FThey had threatened to take X to court 
OL,17,Ffor failing to pay the redundancy money
OL,18,Fthey said they were promised.          
OL,20,FThe company has not commented.         
